<br>
As you enter the Needlite room, set up in the left corner near the ramp out.  Break out a fire pet, Burnout Jabober, then med for a bit.  Once Jabober brings up his fire shield, you're ready to go.<br>
<br>
You can single pull every mob with a nuke except the 2 spawns in the opposite corner of the room.  Once the nuke lands, let Jabober do his job.  Keep him healed with your pet heal series and his damage shield will eat them alive.  Needlites hit for ~15-20 pts of damage, but they swing once per second or so.  Very fast, but low damage.  Since they're taking Jabober's Level+2 every time they contact, the trick is just keeping your pet alive.  Once they start to run, drop a second nuke to finish them.<br>
<br>
Guarding the ramp to the room is a Spore plant.  Stick close to the walls and you avoid it.  It will ignore your pet, but if a Needlite runs up the ramp, there is a chance the plant will kill it and you get no XP.  Had no idea what was killing them at first, then just happened to be close enough to see the message as plant ate my target.<br>
<br>
The center spawn of the room is sometimes the Queen.  Until 24, just /OOC that she is up and someone will come kill her for you.  Pulling her will get adds since she's higher level than the others and her aggro radius is larger.<br>
<br>
Loot isn't exceptional.  Legs and Wings sell for just over 2pp each and dont drop all the time.  Queen drops a semi-decent dagger that you can use (delay 22, damage 9 after disease bonus).<br>
<br>
Once you hit 24 these guys are almost too easy.  They're even-yellow and your new Fire Pet simply destroys them.  At 20 I could pull all but the back 2 spawns, medding between pulls, and have time to med to full before repops in my camp corner.  At 24 I could pull them all w/o worries.<br>
<br>
Last thing, watch your aggro.  Altho they hit light, and you can actually kinda tank them, Needlites hit with such speed that you will not be able to cast once they are on you.  If you get aggro, Tank until Jabober taunts, then try to move away.  If Jabober dies, prepare for a CR. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucmchali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CM Chali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(7/3/02 5:54:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Still there at 29</span><hr size=1> Still there, still blue, still using Fire Pet.<br>
